# Folder Structure Rules

## Folder Naming

### Required: kebab-case
- **MUST** use lowercase with hyphens
- Examples:
  - ✅ `base-panel/`, `upload-feature/`, `creator-badge/`
  - ✅ `dropdown-controls/`, `result-image-preview/`
  - ❌ `basePanel/`, `UploadFeature/`, `creator_badge/`
  - ❌ `base_panel/`, `BasePanel/`

## Organization Strategy

### Prefer Feature-Based Grouping

**✅ CORRECT - Feature-based:**
```
components/
  upload-feature/
    upload-feature.tsx
    upload-button.tsx
    upload-area.tsx
    image-preview.tsx
  creator-badge/
    creator-badge.tsx
    creator-avatar.tsx
    creator-profile-info.tsx
  tools-feature/
    tools-feature.tsx
    color-controls-row.tsx
    hue-bar.tsx
```

**❌ WRONG - Type-based:**
```
components/
  buttons/
    upload-button.tsx
    theme-toggle.tsx
  inputs/
    file-input.tsx
    hex-input.tsx
  panels/
    base-panel.tsx
```

### When Feature-Based Doesn't Fit

If a component is truly shared across features:
- Place in root `components/` directory
- Use kebab-case: `app-header.tsx`, `theme-provider.tsx`
- Or create a `shared/` or `common/` folder if you have many

## Folder Structure Patterns

### Component with Sub-components
```
component-name/
  component-name.tsx      # Main component
  component-header.tsx     # Sub-component
  component-body.tsx       # Sub-component
  index.ts                # Re-exports (named only)
```

### Feature Module
```
feature-name/
  feature-name.tsx         # Main feature component
  feature-input.tsx        # Feature-specific input
  feature-display.tsx      # Feature-specific display
  utils.ts                # Feature-specific utilities (if needed)
  types.ts                 # Feature-specific types (if needed)
```

## Current Structure Assessment

